  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-06-17",
    "date": "2021-10-21T17:29:50Z",
    "text": "Fair Repair Act\n\nThis bill requires an original equipment manufacturer (OEM) to make diagnostic, maintenance, and repair equipment available to independent repair providers.\n\nSpecifically, for digital electronic equipment sold or used in the United States, an OEM shall make documentation, parts, and tools available to independent repair providers in a timely manner and on fair and reasonable terms. Further, if an OEM has made an express warranty for digital electronic equipment with a wholesale price of $100 or more, the OEM must provide such items at an equitable price and convenience of delivery to enable the repair of the equipment during the warranty period.\n\nThe bill provides for enforcement of its provisions by the Federal Trade Commission and state attorneys general."
  },
